Class: Table

insight. Table

new insight.Table(name, element, dataset)

The Table class draws HTML tables from DataSets
Name Type Description
name string A uniquely identifying name for this table
element string The css selector identifying the div container that the table will be drawn in. '#dataTable' for example.
dataset DataSet The DataSet to render this Table from

Methods

#applyTheme(theme){this}

Applies all properties from a theme to the table.
Name Type Description
theme insight.Theme The theme to apply to the table.

This method adds an ascending sort to this Table's rows using the provided function as a comparison

#self.top(){Number}

The number of rows to display. Used in combination with ascending() or descending() to display top or bottom data.
Returns:
The maximum number of top values being displayed.
